subproject.description:
The project is to support the Liberian Gouvernment`s effort in enhancing gouvernance at the district level as well as providing direct support for pro-poor growth initiatives for communities within the general guiding framework of the County Development Agenda (CDA) and in accordance with the Poverty Reduction Strategy (PRS) . Its integrated and area based development approach through four main areas of intervention shall be:
 (1) CONTINUING BUILDING OF CAPACITY IN PARTICIPATORY PLANING AND MANAGEMENT AND LINKING COMMUNITY PLANING WITH DISTRICT AND COUNTY PRIORITIES; 
(2) SUPPORTING THE PROVISION OF BASIC SOCIAL INFRASTRUCTURE FOR LIVELIHOODS SUCH AS FARMS-TO -MARKET ROADS/BRIDGES, MARKET CENTERS, POST-HARVEST FACILITIES, ACCESS TO BASIC HEALTH AND EDUCATION SERVICES AT THE DISTRICT LEVEL;
(3)  PROVIDING SKILLS TRAINING AND MICRO-ENTERPRISE DEVELOPMENT FOR SUSTAINABLE LIVELIHOODS AS WELL AS  PROVIDE SUPPORT FOR FOOD SECURITY AND AGRICULTURAL DEVELOPMENT AND POST-HARVEST;
(4) SUPPORT THE WORK OF THE GOUVERNMENT ESPECIALLY THE MINISTRY OF INTERNAL AFFAIRS IN THE GATHERING OF INFORMATION FOR QUALITATIVE AND QUANTITAIVE PURPOSES ON COMMUNITY FEED-BACK ON DECENTRALISATION.
However, Emphasis will be placed on the support for local economic development initiatives through objective three.  Linkages with the Country Support Teams( CST)and the Local Decentralization and Local Dvelopment (LDLD) initiatives,, especially in the area of capacity development shall be strengthened. 
The project shall also continue to expand on the existing skills of local structures , such as the District Development Committees ( DDCs) in participatory planing through  further training in various participatory tools and methodolgies while the basis of its support shall be priorities identified in the respective CDAs

